---
const words = ['Everyone', 'Has', 'A', 'Brain'];
---

<section id="neuro" class="section neuro-section">
  <div class="container">
    <!-- Scanning title -->
    <div class="scan-title-wrapper">
      <h2 class="section-title neuro-title">NEUROSCIENCE</h2>
      <div class="scan-line"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Terminal panel -->
    <div class="terminal-panel">
      <div class="terminal-header">
        <span class="terminal-dots">
          <span class="dot dot-red"></span>
          <span class="dot dot-yellow"></span>
          <span class="dot dot-green"></span>
        </span>
        <span class="terminal-label">neuro_degree.sh</span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body">
        <p class="term-line"><span class="term-prompt">$</span> cat ~/degree/neuroscience_summary.txt</p>
        <p class="term-line term-output">[01] Neuroanatomy</p>
        <p class="term-line term-output">[02] Behavioral Neuroscience</p>
        <p class="term-line term-output">[03] Insomnia Research</p>
        <p class="term-line term-output">[04] Polysomnography Certification</p>
        <p class="term-line term-output">[05] Phlebotomy Certification</p>
        <p class="term-line term-output">[06] Pharmaceutical Research Studies</p>
        <p class="term-line term-output">&nbsp;</p>
        <p class="term-line term-output">--- 6 items loaded. EOF ---</p>
        <p class="term-line"><span class="term-prompt">$</span> <span class="term-cursor">_</span></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Word cards + paragraph -->
    <div class="topic-grid">
      {words.map((word, i) => (
        <div class="topic-card">
          <div class="topic-header">
            <span class="topic-num">[{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}]</span>
            <h3 class="topic-title">{word}</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="neuro-paragraph boxy-box">
      <p>I am so grateful I got to study neuroscience because everybody has a brain. People will ask me what I want to do with that degree, and while this job is the closest thing to using that degree I've ever had, the truth is it was worth the years of classes just to understand the human condition a bit better.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .neuro-section {
    background-color: #F0F4F0;
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(rgba(0, 200, 100, 0.06) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(0, 200, 100, 0.06) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 24px 24px;
  }

  .scan-title-wrapper {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .neuro-title {
    color: var(--green);
    text-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 204, 68, 0.3);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .scan-line {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 3px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--green), transparent);
    animation: scan-sweep 3s linear infinite;
  }

  @keyframes scan-sweep {
    0% { transform: translateY(0); }
    100% { transform: translateY(60px); }
  }

  /* Terminal */
  .terminal-panel {
    background: #1A1A2E;
    border: var(--border-thick);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-boxy);
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .terminal-header {
    background: #2A2A3E;
    padding: 8px 12px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #333;
  }

  .terminal-dots {
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .dot {
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .dot-red { background: var(--red); }
  .dot-yellow { background: var(--yellow); }
  .dot-green { background: var(--green); }

  .terminal-label {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: #888;
  }

  .terminal-body {
    padding: 16px;
    min-height: 200px;
  }

  .term-line {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--green);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    text-shadow: 0 0 4px rgba(0, 204, 68, 0.4);
  }

  .term-prompt {
    color: var(--yellow);
    margin-right: 8px;
  }

  .term-output {
    color: #88CC88;
    padding-left: 16px;
  }

  .term-cursor {
    animation: blink 1s step-end infinite;
  }

  @keyframes blink {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50% { opacity: 0; }
  }

  /* Topics */
  .topic-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .topic-card {
    background: white;
    border: var(--border-thick);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-boxy);
    padding: 20px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .topic-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .topic-num {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--green);
  }

  .topic-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: #222;
  }

  /* Paragraph */
  .neuro-paragraph {
    margin-top: 28px;
  }

  .neuro-paragraph p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 22px;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .topic-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }
</style>
